            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "1. Downloaded the latest installer from the [releases](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/download/v0.12.2/nvim-win-arm64.msi) here on GitHub.\n2. Ran the installer.\n3. Changed the install directory to my local app data programs<br><br><img width=\"494\" height=\"386\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2af7d8ff-78da-4534-916f-dd96d386e766\" />\n4. Went to finish the installation<br><br><img width=\"494\" height=\"386\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/04600f95-8403-4e40-b19a-34d1f737b759\" />\n5. Received<br><br><img width=\"454\" height=\"191\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b929741f-fc43-4b74-8064-89dacf7601bb\" />\n\nI have installed multiple other programs with user install options, but if Neovim has an option to install to current user, I cannot find it.",
