        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "We had attempted user-local install but reverted it in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/22949 for technical reasons. A later summary is [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/29895#issuecomment-2284725154), where I suggested that we try `ALLUSERS=1`, but I don't think anyone followed up on that. \n\n\n1f58e276 mentions:\n\n> \"Currently the installer already requires administrative privileges and installs into the system-wide ProgramFiles directory\"\n\n\n\nPossible fixes:\n\n1. (breaking) `CPACK_WIX_INSTALL_SCOPE` `\"perUser\"` — installs to `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\Programs\\Neovim`, no UAC. Loses ability to install machine-wide. Breaks existing admin-managed deployments on update.\n2. (ideal) `CPACK_WIX_INSTALL_SCOPE` `\"perUserOrMachine\"` (CMake's WiX wrapper supports this; WiX 3.10+ supports the underlying machinery) — single MSI, user picks at install. Requires changing `CPACK_WIX_UI_REF` from `WixUI_CustomInstallDir` to `WixUI_Advanced` (it's the only built-in dialog set that exposes the scope choice), which would mean reworking or dropping the custom install-dir dialogs already in `cmake.packaging/`.\n\nThis needs some investigation (and a PR) from a Windows user. Then we'll be happy to merge it.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-29T16:42:08Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40034#issuecomment-4577627483",
